text: Courtney Jenaé Woolsey is a Los Angeles-based singer and songwriter."O.C. singer releases second single after YouTube success" Orange County Register. Retrieved 2016-07-14."Courtney Jenaé breaks free with passionate performance" Huntington Beach Independent. Retrieved 2016-07-14. Her songs are published by Sony/ATV. Courtney Jenaé co-wrote “Paradise”"Girls Generation - Paradise" Music Mind. Retrieved 2016-07-14. for Girls Generation’s latest album, Lion Heart, which topped #1 on Billboard’s World Album's Chart."Girls Generation Chart History" Billboard. Retrieved 2016-07-14. She also co-wrote Exo’s 2015 single “Love Me Right” which went platinum in the first week."EXO leader feels more pressured after 2nd platinum" Korea Herald. Retrieved 2016-07-14."Popular group EXO has finally landed in Japan! Shibuya The next Jack the Harajuku!" T-Site News. Retrieved 2015-07-14. She has written songs for numerous artists including “Bad Case Of U” for Bella Thorne, which was featured in Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Road Chip,"Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Road Chip" Soundtrack.net. Retrieved 2016-07-14. “Shake That Brass” by Amber,"Shake that Brass" Musixmatch. Retrieved 2016-07-14. “Magnetic” by Elliott Yamin,"Magnetic" Warner/Chappell Music. Retrieved 2016-07-14. "Crush” by I.O.I, and “Tuk Tok” by Twice. Woolsey co-wrote and was featured on two Blasterjaxx singles, “You Found Me” released by Spinnin’ Records and “Forever” released by Dim Mak. ==Discography== ===As featured artist=== * 2014: Blasterjaxx - "You Found Me" feat.
